Dagannoth Supreme is the Ranged-based Dagannoth King found in the depths of the Waterbirth Island Dungeon, along with fellow Dagannoth Kings, Dagannoth Rex and Dagannoth Prime. Supreme is the only monster to drop the archers ring and seercull. He, along with the other Dagannoth Kings, can also drop the dragon axe.

His Ranged attack sounds like the Water Wave spell when hitting players and, in a similar fashion to Magic attacks, will "splash" if it misses.

Strategy[edit | edit source]

Main article: Dagannoth Kings/Strategies

Dagannoth Supreme is most weak to melee attacks. The best weapons to use primarily are the abyssal whip or tentacle due to its high Strength bonus and fast attack rate, the Saradomin godsword for its special attack, accuracy, and Strength bonus, and Guthan's warspear, which should only be used in conjunction with the full Barrows set to heal. If a player does not possess a Saradomin godsword, a Crystal halberd or Dragon dagger is a good alternative special attack weapon.

Dangers[edit | edit source]

  • The biggest threat when killing Dagannoth Supreme is that Dagannoth Prime may respawn while killing Supreme. To save yourself from Prime's hard-hitting magical attacks, turn on Protect from Magic. You can either stick around or leave up the ladder.
  • Another possible threat is that Dagannoth Rex may respawn instead of Prime. If this happens, try to position Supreme between you and Rex, and if you are a mage, distract him again like in first wave. However, the mage should feel no inclination to kill Rex; just lure him away. Another strategy is to make use of Entangle or ice spells to deal with Rex.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
19 January 2017
(update)

Dagannoth Supreme's range defense was increased from 255 to 550 to reduce twisted bow's effectiveness on it.

5 March 2015
(update | poll)

Dagannoth bones are now noted drops if you have completed the Fremennik Elite Diary.

17 July 2014
(update | poll)

Players can now receive a pet version of this boss after defeating it.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The Dagannoth Supreme's examine text references an entity called the Bukalla. This entity was originally planned to be a tribe of vikings that the Supreme had conquered,[6] but the Bukalla eventually turned out to be a legendary Fremennik warrior.
